<dl id="n09119f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09119f">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09119f"> 119(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Vatican Nero&apos;s garden</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Those who survey with a curious eye the revolutions of mankind may observe that the <mark>gardens and circus of Nero on the Vatican</mark>, which were polluted with the blood of the first Christians, have been rendered still more famous by the triumph and by the abuse of the persecuted religion. <small> Edward Gibbon, <a name="EGDF2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGDF2"><cite title="source">Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</cite></a> (ed. unknown) II, 234 (Chapter XVI)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
